Description: Shoulder sherd of Attic black-figured pottery open vessel, dinos or more probably stamnos; interior: upper part of shoulder reserved and glazed streaky black below; exterior: part of tongue frieze above black-figure decoration consisting of head and hand of woman, with added white flesh and added red fillet, to right, playing auloi; two vine sprays at right.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.0265) (Phase 1)
